description:
Fabulous room in charming modern design apartment, with big living room/kitchen/eating area and 10 foot ceilings throughout. A glassdoor opening to the balcony gives the apartment a very airy and spacious feeling and lets in a lot of light. Hardwood floors.

Sleeps 1 or 2 in the very comfortable queen size bed in the bedroom with high-quality mattress and lines.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is very centrally located in Munich's Au neighborhood. You are 200 meters from the subway stop U2 Fraunhoferstrasse (2 stops to Munich central station), 5 minutes walk to lively district Glockenbach. Glockenbach is wellknown for its trendy fashions boutiques, cosy delis, awesome restaurants and great night life. 8 minutes walk to Viktualienmarkt and Marienplatz. At your feet are cafes, restaurants, dry cleaner, grocery store, hair dresser, the street-car (No. 17) and the subway (U1 an U2). You are in walking distance to the whole downtown area, 200m to the green stripe of the city beach of river Isar.

I am from Munich. I like good food and wine, surf the Isar river or the Atlantic, love long hikes with stay overs and travelling to discover new places of course! I am a fan of design and interior and like to collect little art pieces from my trips.
I am happy to be your host!
Best regards

In 3 minutes walk you are at the Theresienwiese, where the Oktoberfest and Frühlingsfest ( SpringFest - small Oktoberfest ) take place. The queer partyzone is in 10 minutes walking distance. The cultural highlights like the marvellous art gallery Haus Der Kunst or the famous opera Bayerische Staatsoper are at Odeonsplatz, that are eighter to reached in 15 minutes by foot, or simply by the Underground - the station is right next to us.

With the subway (the next station is close by, only 3 minutes walking distance) you are within five minutes in the city center at Marienplatz. A walk of about 25 minutes leads to the charming Glockenbachviertel with many shops and cafes. Enjoy!

name: Beautiful cozy apartment in the heart of Munich
description: Stylish and cozy 2 room apartment with a big balcony in the vibrant, hip neighbourhood Glockenbachviertel near the Isar. Around here you'll find everything you need to have a great time in wonderful Munich and enjoy your stay.
neighborhood_overview:
You will stay in the heart of Munich in the vibrant neighbourhood Glockenbachviertel surrounded by restaurants, (coffee) bars and many shopping opportunities. As the apartment is located overlooking the courtyard, it is really quiet and you can sleep with windows open.
The Isar with its beautiful cycling/running/walking paths leading all the way to and through the English Garden is just a five minute walk away. The river banks offer green spaces for picnics, outdoor activities or a refreshing dip on hot summer days.
To the city centre and the Viktualienmarkt it takes you only about 10 minutes to walk.
For you Oktoberfest people: The "Wiesn" is just one U-Bahn station away or you could also easily walk there (takes about 10-15 min).
The place is also perfect for visitors of trade fairs in Munich as you can directly reach the Messe München in 15 min with the U-Bahn (U2).
host_about:
Hi there!

I'm Lena, a North German girl living in Munich for almost 8 years now. I work as a project manager at a communication agency and part-time yoga teacher. 
Even though I'm from northern Germany and my heart belongs to the sea, I am deeply in love with Munich. It's the perfect city - not too big, not too small. Not too quiet, not too loud & wild. Green and urban. Mountains and lakes. Old and young. But find out for yourselves! Cause this is how you should explore the world. Not by reading books or watching travel channel. But by setting your foot into all these amazing places and experiencing the facets of life through the eyes of locals. So let's get out of our chairs and comfort zones and start exploring!

host_about:
German or English, both is fine :-)
I was born in Stuttgart, studied in Bayreuth and landed in the most beautiful city of Germany: Munich :-)
I came to Munich in May 2011 because I always wanted to live in this beautiful city! And I was lucky to find a job here! :-) Since 5 years I am self-imployed as a massage therapist and sales person for Relight Delight. I work at home and I love it :-)
Like everybody here I love travelling. My hot spots so far have been Australia in 2002, South Africa in 2005, Latin America (Argentina, Bolivia, Perú, Chile) in 2008, India in 2015 & 2017, Myanmar, Cambodia & Vietnam in 2017 and Thailand in 2018.
I also had a short 2 day-visit in Brasil this year (2020), but Corona came in between... :-(

I would love to meet new people from all over the world to have a great time together with lots of fun, great conversations and so on... :-)

My hobbies are Yoga, Hiking (mountain lover), Dancing Salsa Bachata and Kizomba, Running, Snowboarding, Skiing, scuba diving, listening to music and reading a great book,... Best new Hobby: our sweet dog Tochi (see pictures) :-)

CU soon! :-)

The apartment has a 1.40 m wide double bed, a small bathroom with shower and toilet, a kitchenette and a roof terrace.
"Emergency mattress" for third person or child on request.
The apartment is very colorful and imaginative.
On the roof terrace to the east there is sun until about 1 pm, depending on the season.
neighborhood_overview:
The Au is a very quiet neighborhood in top location, known for the Au Dult, a mini folk festival selling antiques and household goods. This takes place three times a year.
You can walk to the Isar floodplains for jogging, walking or swimming in five minutes.
Gardener's Square in 15 min walk.
Also the Müllersche Volksbad.
An outdoor swimming pool is also nearby from May.
Shopping facilities are within walking distance, weekly market with regional providers twice a week.
There are plenty of beer gardens, cafes and restaurants in the neighborhood, and an even larger selection is available from the Isar.
A great starting point to explore the city.

description:
Right in between Prinzregentenplatz and Max-Weber-Platz is where we call our home.

Green Parks nearby, perfect public transport connection and a diverse selection of shops, cafés and restaurants - thats why we love it here.

Our 3 bedroom (+living room) is the ideal place to stay when visiting munich.

This bedroom faced out west and has access to the small balcony to the court yard.

neighborhood_overview:
Located between Prinzregentenplatz and Max-Weber-Platz, this gem is in prime location and only a 10 Minute Bikeride from the city Center.
Looking out on a green park and a pool - the location offers plenty of outdoor spots in the close vacinity. Walk for about 5 minutes and you'll arrive at the Friedensengel and the surrounding parks along the Isar river.

Restaurants and shops are close by - both along Prinzregentenstraße and in Bogenhausen and along Einsteinstraße. Explore the charming corners of Haidhausen - with small boutiques and stores. Here you will be loured in by the sweet smells of delicious baked goods, coffee and delicatessen from local cafés and bakaries.

Public Transport will take you to the prime spots in town - whether the artsy streets of Schwabing via the Bus lines, Glockenbachviertel by tram or the U-Bahn/subway, which will take you into the city center in just 5 Minutes.

Population

BMW

Euro Industrial Park

Olympic area

Isar floodplains

The neighborhood in Schwanthalerhöhe is full of bars, restaurants and small store. Shopping is within walking distance in a few minutes.

name: Wohnung an der Theresienwiese
description:
Welcome to my cozy and bright 2 room apartment directly at the Munich Octoberfest. In the middle of Munich's smallest neighborhood, the Westend, you will find many nice restaurants, cute bars and small stores. Shopping facilities are even directly across the street. The tram, city train and metro are also right around the corner.

In my apartment you will find a fully equipped kitchen, a living room with desk and a couch corner with beamer (TV) and a nice spacious bedroom plus a balcony.
neighborhood_overview: Not sure if you have been in Munich before but from my place you can reach a lot of things by feet. Main train station is about 10mins by feet away, city center is about 20mins by feet away. Isar river is also about 15-20mins by feet. Westpark (best for autumn walks) is about 20mins by feet as well. There is also a big shopping center right on the other side of the street which has supermarkets, clothing stores, cafes and bistros and more. In the same street walking to the west, there are quite some restaurants and cafes. I can really recommend Bean Batter (for cafe and breakfast) togather (cafe and breakfast), Das Kulinariat (for dinner), Schwarzer Dackel (for drinks), Punto Gelato (for icecream) and Zur Schwalbe (for lunch and dinner).

name: 3Room + 2Bath Apt + Breakfast in Center of Munich
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment in centrally located in the Maxvorstadt neighborhood. Maxvorstadt is directly next to the historic old town. Odeonsplatz is 10min by foot, famous Marienplatz is 15 mins by foot.

Nearby, you will find Maxvorstadt's many streets filled with hip restaurants and cafes. As both big universities of Munich are located in Maxvorstadt, the area radiates a young and international vibe.

Also, Maxvorstadt features Munich's most renowned museums such as the 3 Pinakotheken for medieval, 19-20th century and modern art, the Neue Sammlung for industrial design, and the new NS-Dokumentationszentrum that explains the controversial role of Munich during WWII.

All are in a short walking distance from the apartment, and I am happy to suggest you more hidden places based on your interests.
host_about:
I've lived in the US, grew up in Spain, but I was born in Ukraine! I love traveling, and usually use Airbnb when choosing accommodation. I believe it's a great way to meet locals and have an authentic experience.
Occasionally I host guests myself which I truly enjoy.

neighborhood_overview: The Glockenbach district is the most vibrant part of Munich. It has countless amazing restaurants (Recommendation: Maximilian, Das Maria and Junge Römer) and trendy bars (Recommendation: Loretta Bar, Zephyr Bar and Frau Bartels) as well as supermarkets, drug stores and lovely shops (You can totally buy a Lederhosen or Dirndl here). The neighborhood is very diverse from students to young families to old couples and it is the heart of Munich´s LGBTQ scene. From our place its only a three minute walk the subway station "Fraunhoferstraße" (U1/U2), which takes you all over Munich (two stops to the main station). To me the best part about our location is the five minute walk down to the Isar river (just across the Reichenbachbrücke). It's a super nice spot to spend a day in the sun, go swimming, play spikeball or simply watch the sunset.

name: Gemütliche Wohnung in Schwabing - München
description:
The studio is in a quiet place in the direct area of Olympiapark and close to Hohenzollernplatz metro station.
Messe München can be reached directly from Hohenzollernplatz U-Bahn [subway] station without changing trains.
You'll be in the
Downtown as well as numerous bars,
Restaurants.
There are a nearby
Grocery (Rewe), a pharmacy and a cleaning.
A small west-facing balcony lets you enjoy the evening sun perfectly.
host_about:
Hallo zusammen!
Ich bin Italienerin und wohne dauerhaft in der wunderbaren Stadt München.

Reisen ist meine Leidenschaft. Vor allem liebe ich Afrika, das Meer, Outdoor Abenteuer, leckeres Essen und Kulturhighlights.

Gäste aus aller Welt zu empfangen und ihnen eine stilvolle Wohnung im Herzen von München zu bieten, ist eine der coolsten Sachen überhaupt!
Ich bin ein unkomplizierter Mensch. Als Gastgeberin helfe ich meinen Gästen immer und versuche, ihnen das bestmögliche Erlebnis zu bieten. Da ich oft und gerne reise, verstehe ich, was die Leute von meiner Wohnung erwarten. 

Ich lerne gerne neue Leute kennen, zum Beispiel auf Reisen und jetzt auch zu Hause.
Auf neuen Kontakten und unvergesslichen Eindrücken freue ich mich sehr! 

Ich stehe gerne für Hilfe zur Verfügung und gebe euch gerne Anregungen, wie ihr München von seiner authentischen Seite entdecken könnt.

Ich freue mich auf nette Gäste und Begegnungen und einen respektvollen Umgang mit meinem Hab und Gut.

Liebe Grüße und ich freue mich auf euch!

The attractive multi-family house is located on a traffic-calmed one-way street in a self-contained area with well-kept green space and illuminated paths. There is a smaller playground in the center for small children of the residents of the complex.

Oberföhring is a district in the north-east of Munich and belongs to the Bogenhausen district. Oberföhring is known for its attractive proximity
(5 min. walk) to the Isar and the northern part of the English Garden.

You have your own infrastructure here with several shopping options such as Edeka, Aldi, Rewe, dm, hardware store, etc., which can be quickly reached in the Unterföhring/Feringastraße commercial area within 5 minutes by car or 10-15 minutes on foot.

The airport can be easily reached by S-Bahn (S 8 approx. 25 minutes) and by car (approx. 25 minutes).

neighborhood_overview:
The popular district of Hadern is on the southwest of Munich. Adjacent to the Sendling district, Hadern is very well served by all public transportation through the subway line 6, which leads to Klinikum Großhadern. In 10 minutes you are at the Sendlinger Tor, or a few minutes later in the heart of the Old Town, Marienplatz. Also, the proximity to the Mittleren Ring and the Lindau and Garmisch motorways, makes Hadern an excellent starting point for trips to the beautiful Bavarian foothills with its mountains and lakes. Without having to drive through wide industrial belts or to cross the city, you can easily reach Munich's house mountains for skiing in winter Munich's house mountains or swim in 20 minutes on Lake Starnberg in summer.

Wir sind beide Kunsthistoriker aus München. Ich arbeite als Ausstellungsreferentin für Angewandte Kunst und Kunsthandwerk, Thomas ist Möbelrestaurator. Deshalb gefiel uns die Lage der Wohnung und der schöne Altbau. Wir finden es auch immer nett, etwas Kontakt zu Menschen, die in der Stadt leben, zu bekommen, evtl. den einen oder and anderen Tipp zu erhalten. Wir freuen uns auf das Kunsthistorische, das kaiserliche Hofimmobiliendepot,das MAK und natürlich abends auf die Kneipen und Beiserl in Wien. 

Thomas liebt die Berge, Sommers wie Winters, ich eher nur im Winter zum Skifahren. 

viele Grüße 
Angela

host_about:
Hi i'm Faissal! My friends call me Faissalito! I'm a moroccan guy living in Munich for already more than 17 years. 
I grew up in Casablanca, where african lifestyle meets the fast pace of a metropolis. But I must confess the easy-going way of life corresponds more my way of seeing things ;)
As the ocean has forever been my home, water is my preferred element. I became a passionated bodyboarder over the years. My hobby drives me to travel around the world, always eager to find the perfect spot to surf. 
I love to meet new people from different cultural backgrounds who share their wisdoms about life. Generally open-minded and with a smile on my face, I see airBnB as a perfect opportunity to give everyone the chance to see new places and to make new experiences. I am happy enough to have my own apartment in Munich and excited to share it with you.

You like to party during the day, but want your peace at night? Welcome to our cozy flatshare.

It takes you 2 min to the subway + 8 minutes directly in front of the entrance of the Oktoberfest.

Enjoy your stay in a huge room of 20sqm incl. direct access to a balcony and a full size dining table.

The appartment is fully equipped, so there is not much to bring.

Important:
As I am working the whole time, you need to pick up the key close to Marienplatz (right in the center - 15 min away)

name: Amour Room in Munich
description:
The apartment is located in Schwabing, one of Munich's trendiest and most vibrant districts. The distance to the Theresienwiese, where the Oktoberfest takes place, is about 15 minutes by public transport.

The apartment is very spacious, furnished with love for detail.

Kitchen is fully equipped, balcony very nicely decorated and toilet separate from the bathroom.
